.TH ZOPEN-BUILD "1" "June 2026" "zopen tools 0.8.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
zopen-build \- manual page for zopen-build 0.8.5
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B zopen-build
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
zopen\-build is a general purpose build script to be used with the
zopen community ports.
.SS "Option:"
.TP
\fB\-\-build\fR LINE
LINE may be dev or stable. This is the build line
to build off of.
.TP
\fB\-\-buildtype\fR TYPE
TYPE may be release or debug.  The default is release.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-clean\fR
Deletes all of the build output and forces
reconfigure with next build.
.TP
\fB\-\-ccache\fR
Enable ccache for clang builds to speed up
recompilation.
.TP
\fB\-\-comp\fR COMP
COMP may be xlclang, clang, go, java
python. The default is clang.
.TP
\fB\-e\fR ENV_FILE
source ENV_FILE instead of buildenv to establish
build environment.
.TP
\fB\-E\fR, \fB\-\-editable\fR
enable editing of the executable (adds \fB\-Wl\fR,\-bedit=yes to LDFLAGS).
.TP
\fB\-\-instrument\fR
instruments the application with option \fB\-finstrument\-functions\fR (clang only)
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\-rebuild\fR
forces a rebuild, including running bootstrap
and configure again.
.TP
\fB\-\-forcepatchapply\fR
force apply the patches, where rejected patches are
placed into a corresponding file of the same name,
with the .rej extension.
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-get\-source\fR
get the source and apply patch without building.
.TP
\fB\-gp\fR, \fB\-\-generate\-pax\fR
generate a pax.Z file based on the install contents.
.TP
\fB\-gr\fR, \fB\-\-generate\-rpm\fR
generate an RPM package from the pax archive.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR, \-?
print this information.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-set\-active\fR
do not change the pinned version.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-install\-deps\fR
do not install project's runtime dependencies.
.TP
\fB\-\-oci\fR
build and publish an OCI image to $ZOPEN_IMAGE_REGISTRY.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR
exec a shell before running configure. Useful when
manually building ports.
.TP
\fB\-\-sign\-pax\fR, \fB\-sp\fR
This option signs the pax file.
ZOPEN_GPG_SECRET_KEY_FILE, ZOPEN_GPG_SECRET_KEY_PASSPHRASE_FILE
and ZOPEN_GPG_PUBLIC_KEY_FILE must be set for signing the file.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
run in verbose mode.
.TP
\fB\-vv\fR
run in very verbose mode (sets environment variables
V=1 and VERBOSE=1).
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-upgradedeps\fR
upgrade all dependencies by running zopen install.
.PP
The specifics of how the tool works can be controlled through environment
variables. The only environment variables you _must_ specify are to tell
zopen\-build where the source is, and in what format type the source is stored.
By default, the environment variables are defined in a file named buildenv
in the root directory of the [PACKAGE]port github repository.
.PP
To see a fully functioning zopen community sample port see:
https://github.com/zopencommunity/zotsampleport
.PP
User\-Provided environment variables:
.SS "Required:"
.TP
ZOPEN_BUILD_LINE
Specify the default build line, either 'DEV' or 'STABLE'
.TP
ZOPEN_CATEGORIES
Specify a space\-delimited list of applicable categories.
Valid categories:
('security development language ai core utilities editor source_control networking webframework database devops graphics math testing documentation library compression json monitoring shell build_system ai')
.TP
ZOPEN_DEV_DEPS
Required IF ZOPEN_BUILD_LINE='DEV'.
Specify the dev build dependencies
.TP
ZOPEN_DEV_URL
Required IF ZOPEN_BUILD_LINE='DEV'. Specify the dev
build URL (either git or tarball).
.TP
ZOPEN_STABLE_DEPS
Required IF ZOPEN_BUILD_LINE='STABLE'.
Specify the stable build dependencies.
.TP
ZOPEN_STABLE_URL
Required IF ZOPEN_BUILD_LINE='STABLE'. Specify the
stable build URL (either git or tarball).
.SS "Optional:"
.TP
ZOPEN_SOURCE_URL
If set, use this as ZOPEN_URL before checking
ZOPEN_DEV_URL or ZOPEN_STABLE_URL.
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_CFLAGS
C compiler flags to append to CFLAGS (defaults to '').
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_CPPFLAGS
C,C++ pre\-processor flags to append to CPPFLAGS.
(defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_CXXFLAGS
C++ compiler flags to append to CXXFLAGS.
(defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_LDFLAGS
C,C++ linker flags to append to LDFLAGS.
(defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_LIBS
C,C++ libraries to append to LIBS. (defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_BOOTSTRAP
Bootstrap program to run. If skip is specified,
no bootstrap step is performed.
(defaults to './bootstrap')
.TP
ZOPEN_BOOTSTRAP_OPTS
Options to pass to bootstrap program.
(defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_CHECK
Check program to run. If skip is specified,
no check step is performed.
(defaults to 'make')
.TP
ZOPEN_CHECK_MINIMAL
Check program will not be passed CFLAGS, LDFLAGS,
CPPFLAGS options but will get them from env vars.
.TP
ZOPEN_CHECK_OPTS
Options to pass to check program.
(defaults to 'check')
.TP
ZOPEN_CHECK_TIMEOUT
Timeout limit in seconds for the check program.
(defaults to '12600')
.TP
ZOPEN_CLEAN
Clean up program to run.
(defaults to 'make')
.TP
ZOPEN_CLEAN_OPTS
Options to pass to clean up  program.
(defaults to 'clean')
.TP
ZOPEN_CONFIGURE
Configuration program to run. If skip is
specified, no configuration step is performed.
(defaults to './configure')
.TP
ZOPEN_CONFIGURE_MINIMAL
Configuration program will not be passed CFLAGS,
LDFLAGS, CPPFLAGS options but will get them from
env vars.
.TP
ZOPEN_CONFIGURE_OPTS
Options to pass to configuration program.
(defaults to '\-\-prefix=${ZOPEN_INSTALL_DIR}')
.TP
ZOPEN_EXTRA_CONFIGURE_OPTS
Extra configure options to pass to configuration
program. (defaults to '')
.TP
ZOPEN_INSTALL
Installation program to run. If skip is specified,
no installation step is performed.
(defaults to 'make')
.TP
ZOPEN_INSTALL_OPTS
Options to pass to installation program.
(defaults to 'install')
.TP
ZOPEN_MAKE
Build program to run. If skip is specified,
no build step is performed.
(defaults to 'make')
.TP
ZOPEN_MAKE_MINIMAL
Build program will not be passed CFLAGS, LDFLAGS,
CPPFLAGS options but will get them from env vars.
.TP
ZOPEN_MAKE_OPTS
Options to pass to build program.
(defaults to '\-j${ZOPEN_NUM_JOBS}')
.TP
ZOPEN_PATCH_DIR
Specify directory from which patches should be applied.
.SS "Optional settings for installation:"
.TP
ZOPEN_RUNTIME_DEPS
Runtime z/OS Open Tool dependencies to be installed
alongside the tool.
.TP
ZOPEN_SETUP_NO_REPLACE
If set, do not replace hardcoded paths with
placeholders.
.TP
ZOPEN_SYSTEM_PREREQ
System prerequisites, supply the name of the prereq
scripts under /u/tejas/new_zopen/zostools_dev/doc/meta/bin/../include/prereq.sh
.PP
Restricted Usage \- only set in ports if necessary
.TP
ZOPEN_DONT_ADD_ZOSLIB_DEP
Set to avoid adding zoslib as a dependency.
.SS "Restricted Usage - only SET by metaport, otherwise READ ONLY:"
.TP
ZOPEN_INSTALL_DIR
Installation directory to pass to configuration.
(defaults to '${ZOPEN_PKGINSTALL}/<pkg>/<pkg>')
.TP
ZOPEN_NUM_JOBS
Number of jobs that can be run in parallel
(defaults to half the CPUs on the system)
.SS "Restricted Usage (clang):"
.TP
ZOPEN_CFLAGS
C compiler flags. (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_CPPFLAGS
C/C++ pre\-processor flags. (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_CXXFLAGS
C++ compiler flags. (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_LDFLAGS
C/C++ linker flags. (default set by dependency)
.SS "Restricted Usage (phpport):"
.TP
ZOPEN_GIT_SETUP
Specify whether git files should be added to a local
repo or if this will be done manually. (defaults to Y)
.SS "Restricted Usage (tclport):"
.TP
ZOPEN_SRC_DIR
Specify a relative source directory to cd to for
bootstrap, configure, build, check, install.
(defaults to '.')
.SS "Restricted Usage (meta):"
.TP
ZOPEN_IMAGE_DOCKERFILE_NAME
Dockerfile name. (default: Dockerfile)
.TP
ZOPEN_IMAGE_DOCKER_NAME
Docker/podman tool name. (default: podman)
.TP
ZOPEN_IMAGE_REGISTRY
Docker image registry to an OCI image to
(use with \fB\-\-oci\fR option)
.TP
ZOPEN_IMAGE_REGISTRY_ID
The ID to authenticate to the Docker image
registry. (use with \fB\-\-oci\fR option)
.TP
ZOPEN_IMAGE_REGISTRY_KEY_FILE
The file containing authentication key to the
Docker image registry. (use with \fB\-\-oci\fR option)
.TP
ZOPEN_LOG_DIR
The directory to store build logs.
(defaults to '/log')
.TP
ZOPEN_SHELL
Specify an alternate shell to use if \fB\-s\fR
option specified. (defaults to \fI\,/bin/sh\/\fP)
.SS "Git variables:"
.TP
ZOPEN_DEV_BRANCH
The branch that the git repo should checkout.
(default is repo default)
.TP
ZOPEN_DEV_TAG
The tag that the git repo should checkout as a branch.
(optional)
.TP
ZOPEN_STABLE_BRANCH
The branch that the stable repo should checkout.
(default is repo default)
.TP
ZOPEN_STABLE_TAG
The tag that the git repo should checkout as a branch.
(optional)
.TP
ZOPEN_CLONE_SUBMODULES
Set to yes to recursively clone submodules.
.TP
ZOPEN_CLONE_FULL
Set to yes to perform a full clone as opposed to the
default shallow clone (depth of 1).
.SS "Currently unused:"
.TP
ZOPEN_DEV_TYPE
The type of package to download. Valid types are
TARBALL, BARE and GIT.
.TP
ZOPEN_STABLE_TYPE
The type of package to download. Valid types are
TARBALL, BARE and GIT.
.SS "Deprecated:"
.TP
ZOPEN_CC
C compiler. (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_CXX
C++ compiler. (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_DEPS
Alternate environment variable instead of
ZOPEN_TARBALL_DEPS or ZOPEN_GIT_DEPS.
.TP
ZOPEN_GIT_BRANCH
The branch that the git repo should checkout.
.TP
ZOPEN_GIT_DEPS
Space\-delimited set of source packages this tarball
package depends on to build.
(required if ZOPEN_TYPE=GIT)
.TP
ZOPEN_GIT_TAG
The tag that the git repo should checkout as a branch.
.TP
ZOPEN_GIT_URL
The fully qualified URL that the git repo should be
cloned from. (required if ZOPEN_TYPE=GIT)
.TP
ZOPEN_LIBS
C/C++ libraries (default set by dependency)
.TP
ZOPEN_TARBALL_DEPS
Space\-delimited set of source packages this git package
depends on to build. (required if ZOPEN_TYPE=TARBALL)
.TP
ZOPEN_TARBALL_URL
The fully qualified URL that the tarball should be
downloaded from. (required if ZOPEN_TYPE=TARBALL)
.TP
ZOPEN_TYPE
The type of package to download. Valid types are
TARBALL, BARE and GIT.
.TP
ZOPEN_URL
Alternate environment variable instead of
ZOPEN_TARBALL_URL or ZOPEN_GIT_URL.
.PP
User\-Provided functions:
.SS "Required:"
.TP
zopen_check_results
This function runs after the 'check' step
of the build and must print out expected
and actual failures.
.TP
zopen_get_version
This function returns the version of the
tool in accordance with semantic versioning.
.SS "Optional:"
.TP
zopen_append_to_env
This function runs as part of generation
of the .env file. The output of the
function is appended to .env.
.TP
zopen_append_to_setup
This function runs as part of generation of
the setup.sh file. The output of the
function is appended to setup.sh.
.TP
zopen_append_to_validate_install
This function runs as part of generation of
the install_test.sh file. The output of the
function is appended to install_test.sh
script.
.TP
zopen_install_caveats
This function is run post install. All stdout
messages are captured and added to the
metadata.json as installation caveats.
.TP
zopen_append_to_zoslib_env
This function runs as part of generation of
the C function zoslib_env_hook, which can
be used to set environment variables before
main is run.
.TP
zopen_init
This function runs after code is downloaded
and patched but before the code is built.
.TP
zopen_post_buildenv
This function runs after the 'buildenv' is
processed.
.TP
zopen_post_extract
This function runs when an archive containing
the source to build has been uncompressed.
.TP
zopen_post_install
This function runs after the 'install' step
of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_build
This function runs before the 'make' step
of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_check
This function runs before the 'check' step
of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_configure
This function runs before the 'configure'
step of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_install
This function runs before the 'install'
step of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_patch
This function runs before the 'patch' step
of the build is run.
.TP
zopen_pre_terminate
This function runs before 'zopen build'
terminates.
.SS "SEE ALSO:"
.IP
zopen(1)
zopen\-alt(1)
zopen\-init(1)
zopen\-install(1)
zopen\-list(1)
zopen\-remove(1)
.PP
